<author><name><![CDATA[juniper7]]></name></author>
<updated>2016-11-13T17:12:10-07:00</updated>
<published>2016-11-13T17:12:10-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7077&amp;p=30337#p30337</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7077&amp;p=30337#p30337"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Windows 7 XP Luna skin]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7077&amp;p=30337#p30337"><![CDATA[
One or two others were attempting the same thing with a 7 style Luna menu.<br />Does not look if it ever got completed?<br /><br />Whenever modifying a menu, make sure to turn on &quot;Report skin errors&quot; in the &quot;General Behavior&quot; tab.<br />Sometimes CSM program will tell you if a wrong size bitmap is being used.<br />Most alignments have to be pixel perfect measurements, or could end up with a white skinless menu showing.<br />I find it's best to make a couple changes at a time, save it, and see what it looks like. <br />Save a copy in a safe place that won't get overwritten after a number a changes.<br />The worst thing to do, is make so many changes at once, without a backup copy. <br />Then one tries it and find it's all buggered up, without knowing what crippled skin. <br />I've done that many times, and paid the price for being a lazy backup bum. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />As Jcee mentioned, going classic to 7 style is a lot more complex, with more bitmaps / text required.<br />Going other way CSM program just disregards 7 style bitmaps / text. There wont be any classic one column, <br />user picture out of whack, and some 7 style list text, has to be converted back to submenu text. <br /><br /><br />There are restrictions as to what 7 style can do. <br /><br />Pluses and minuses.<br />Like no icons on second column<br /><br />Has separate power button<br /><br />No single column<br /><br />Has a separate programs button<br />User picture is more or less stuck in center of second column.<br /><br />User name can still work, just put in left column.<br /><br />Instead of jump and search submenus, they become part of the main menu.<br />So three main menu bitmaps. Classic Luna (Ivo's), has a main bitmap for single, and another for two column.<br /><br />The 7 style submenu is inside main menu, or can have fly out menu.<br /><br />Due to a wide variety of computer sizes, with different dot per inch specs, you might get skin to work at standard 96 DPI,<br />then all alignment goes out on 120, 144, 192 DPI. <br />Ivo has made it so there is a 144 HDPI option that kicks in to use bigger images and alignments. <br /><br />Can't have icons down at bottom like original XP menus.<br />There is a way to carefully put a picture of icon in the power button. It's very tricky to stop the image from stretching distortion.<br /><br />Another way is have icon picture as an emblem, that can be placed close to shutdown button that shows on menu, or make shutdown arrow as icon picture.<br /><br /><br />I would like to help you out, but for the next week or so, I'm working on a StarFox Classic menu. <br />Damn brain, I typed FireFox first.<img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br />I might even make a 7 style one of it as well.<br />That way, I can refresh myself, so I can help you later.<br /><br />Until later, bye. <br /><br />By the way, my construction skin is probably more messy than yours, at this point. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Sun Nov 13, 2016 5:12 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
